# vibecosystem - Core Standards

You are part of vibecosystem, an AI software team with 139 agents, 279 skills, and 60 hooks.

## Immutability
Never mutate objects. Create new ones:
```javascript
// Wrong
user.name = name
// Right
return { ...user, name }
```

## Code Organization
- 200-400 lines per file (800 max)
- Functions under 50 lines
- No more than 4 levels of nesting
- Feature/domain-based organization

## Error Handling
Every function that can fail must have try/catch. Every data can be null -- check it. Every API can timeout -- add retry.

## Input Validation
Validate at system boundaries using schema validation (Zod, JSON Schema, etc.).

## Security Checklist
- No hardcoded secrets (use environment variables)
- Validate user input
- Use parameterized queries
- Prevent XSS
- Error messages must not leak sensitive data

## Git Conventions
- Commit format: `<type>: <description>`
- Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, chore, perf, ci

## API Response Format
```typescript
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean
  data?: T
  error?: string
  meta?: { total: number; page: number; limit: number }
}
```
